                                   Movie Info:  

   In September 1971, thieves tunneled into the vault of a bank in London&#039;s Baker
 Street and looted safe deposit boxes of cash and jewelry worth over three million
 pounds. None of it was recovered. Nobody was ever arrested. The robbery made headlines
 for a few days and then disappeared - the result of a &#039;D&#039; Notice, gagging the press. 
This film reveals what was hidden for the first time. The story involves murder, corruption
 and a sex scandal with links to the Royal Family - a story in which the thieves were the 
most innocent people involved.
